stylometry: Simulation model is a computer model that imitates a rel-life situation. This model is like other mathetmatical models, but incorporates uncertainty in one or more inpout variables. When we run a simulation, we allow these random input variables to take on various values, and we keep track of any resulting output variables of interest. In this way we are able to see how the outputs vary as a function of the varying inputs. A great benefit of this it that it enables us to answer these types of what-it questions without actually changing a physical system.
